    <descriptionText><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px; padding:0 0 0 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Identifying Areas of Value Creation</Introtext><welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">We’re making a big change in our expectations of who in the office should know the details of insurance coverage and formularies.  Previously, we relied on the prescribers.  However, we’re now transitioning that responsibility to some of the non-prescribing staff, namely, the nurses and two staff members from the front office.  These staff will be responsible for communicating the information to the prescribers prior to the patient visit, and for confirming coverage of prescriptions before they are given to the patient.  If this works well, it will have a huge impact on our efficiency and on patient satisfaction.</welcomeText>]]></descriptionText>
